2018, scoring 15 points off the bench on 6-of-7 shooting in an 83\u201362 win over [[Robert Morris Colonials men's basketball|Robert Morris]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Nov 6, 2018 - Robert Morris 62, USC 83 |url=https://basketball.realgm.com/ncaa/boxscore/2018-11-06/Robert-Morris-at-USC/310384 |publisher=[[RealGM]] |accessdate=December 29, 2018 |date=November 6, 2018}}</ref> On November 20, against [[Missouri State Bears men's basketball|Missouri State]], he suffered a quadriceps contusion. He returned on December 1 versus [[Nevada Wolf Pack men's basketball|Nevada]] but left after 4 minutes because he was hindered by the injury.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kaufman |first1=Joey |title=USC\u2019s Kevin Porter Jr. still sidelined with thigh injury, but eyes a late December return |url=https://www.ocregister.com/2018/12/20/uscs-kevin-porter-jr-still-sidelined-with-thigh-injury-but-eyes-a-late-december-return/ |website=[[Orange County Register]] |accessdate=December 29, 2018 |date=December 20, 2018}}</ref> He missed nine games with a quad contusion, and returned again on January 10, 2019, scoring 5 points in 25 minutes.<ref>{{cite web |title=USC vs. Oregon State - Box Score |url=http://www.espn.com/mens-college-basketball/boxscore?gameId=401087126 |publisher=[[ESPN]] |accessdate=January 14, 2019 |date=January 10, 2019}}</ref> Three days later, however, he was suspended indefinitely by USC for \"personal conduct issues.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bonagura |first1=Kyle |title=USC freshman Kevin Porter Jr. suspended indefinitely, coach says |url=http://www.espn.com/mens-college-basketball/story/_/id/25754912/kevin-porter-jr-usc-trojans-suspended-game-vs-oregon-ducks |publisher=[[ESPN]] |accessdate=January 14, 2019 |date=January 13, 2019}}</ref> Regardless, Porter stated that he would finish the season with the team<ref>{{cite web |last1=McCollough |first1=J. Brady |title=USC\u2019s Kevin Porter Jr. responds to his indefinite suspension from the team |url=https://www.baltimoresun.com/s