beat Cavaliers in season opener|date=October 23, 2019|website=ESPN.com|accessdate=October 23, 2019}}</ref> Porter scored a career high 18 points in 31 minutes in a 123 to 105 loss to the New York Knicks. He finished the game with 18 points, 4 rebounds, 2 assists, and a steal.\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{NBA player statistics legend}}\n\n===College===\n{{NBA player statistics start}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2018\u201319 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2018\u201319]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2018\u201319 USC Trojans men's basketball team|USC]]\n| 21 || 4 || 22.1 || .471 || .412 || .522 || 4.0 || 1.4 || .8 || .5 || 9.5\n{{S-end}}\n\n==Player profile==\nSince the start of the [[2018\u201319 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2018\u201319 season]], Porter was projected as a first-round prospect for the [[2019 NBA draft]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Woo |first1=Jeremy |title=NBA Draft Watch: USC's Kevin Porter Jr. Deserves Your Attention |url=https://www.si.com/nba/2018/11/12/nba-draft-2019-prospect-usc-kevin-porter-jr-deserves-your-attention |website=[[Sports Illustrated]] |accessdate=December 29, 2018 |date=November 12, 2018}}</ref> He looks up to [[James Harden]], as both players are left-handed.<ref name=\"theringer.com\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Cleveland Cavaliers current roster}}\n{{2019 NBA draft}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Porter, Kevin Jr.}}\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:African-American basketball players]]\n[[Category:American men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Basketball players from Washington (state)]]\n[[Category:Cleveland Cavaliers players]]\n[[Category:Milwaukee Bucks draft picks]]\n[[Category:Shooting guards]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Seattle]]\n[[Category:USC Trojans men's basketball players]]\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix dead link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Porter_Jr."}
